{{Infobox journal | title = Australian Journal of Earth Sciences | cover = | editor = A.S. Andrew | discipline = [[Earth science]] | former_names = Journal of the Geological Society of Australia | abbreviation = Aust. J. Earth Sci. | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[Geological Society of Australia]] | country = Australia | frequency = 8/year | history = 1953-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.417 | impact-year = 2012 | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=taje20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/taje20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/taje20 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 45381897 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0812-0099 | eISSN = 1440-0952 }} The '''''Australian Journal of Earth Sciences''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] that is published eight times per year by [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[Geological Society of Australia]]. The journal broadly covers the [[earth science]]s. The [[editor-in-Chief]] is A.S. Andrew ([[New South Wales]]). It was established in 1953 as the ''Journal of the Geological Society of Australia'' and obtained its current name in 1984.
