==World Economic Forum list / economic issues== In keeping with their economy-centered view, the [[World Economic Forum]] formulated a list of 10 most pressing points in 2016: <ref name="Hutt Content 2016">{{cite web | last=Hutt | first=Rosamond | last2=Content | first2=Formative | title=What are the 10 biggest global challenges? | website=World Economic Forum | date=2016-01-21 | url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2016/01/what-are-the-10-biggest-global-challenges/ | access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref> #[[Food security]] #[[Inclusive growth]] #Future of work/[[unemployment]] #[[Climate change]] #[[Global financial crisis]] #Future of the internet/[[Fourth Industrial Revolution]] #[[Gender equality]] #[[Global trade]] and investment and [[regulatory]] frameworks #Long-term [[investment]]/[[Investment strategy]] #Future [[healthcare]] {{see also|sustainable growth|green economy|global recession|International Monetary Fund|World Trade Organization}}
==Environmental issues== {{main|List of environmental issues}} Theories like the [[World-systems theory|world-system theory]] and the [[Gaia hypothesis]] focus on the inter-dependency aspect of environmental and economic issues. Among the most evident environmental problems are:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conserve-energy-future.com/15-current-environmental-problems.php|title=15 Current Environmental Problems That Our World is Facing - Conserve Energy Future|first=|last=Rinkesh|date=27 June 2014|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://inhabitat.com/why-we-need-earth-day-7-most-pressing-environmental-problems-we-need-to-solve/|title=The World's 6 Most Pressing Environmental Issues|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrdc.org/issues/|title=NRDC - Our Work|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalissues.org/issue/168/environmental-issues|title=Environmental Issues — Global Issues|publisher=}}</ref> *[[overpopulation]] *[[resource depletion]] *[[pollution]] *[[water pollution]] *[[waste]] and [[waste disposal]] *[[ocean acidification]] *[[acid rain]] *[[ozone layer depletion]] *[[global warming]]/[[climate change]] *[[loss of biodiversity]] and [[habitat loss]] *[[deforestation]] *[[urban sprawl]]
No single issue can be analysed or treate isolated from the others.<ref>http://www.geni.org/globalenergy/issues/global/major-global-issues-diagram-lg.jpg</ref> For example, habitat loss and climate change adversely affect biodiversity. Deforestation and pollution are direct consequences of overpopulation and both, in turn, affect biodiversity. While overpopulation locally leads to [[rural flight]], this is more than counterbalanced by accelerating [[urbanization]] and urban sprawl.
{{see also|zero population growth|green economy|overconsumption}}
